Description: String of beads of various shapes and dimensions; beads of glazed composition include globular beads, some with traces of green glaze, short and standard cylinder beads, one moulded, other beads of this material consist of one of irregular shape with impressed decoration, a green wedjat-eye bead, a barrel bead with incised decoration, a green djed-pillar bead, and a blue diamond-shaped bead; the string also contains a number of shells, both complete and sliced.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.86, p.187, pl.29)
